# local dev artifacts
debug.log

# parquet snapshots fetched from CDN at dev time
public/data/

# Per-block state snapshots — auto-generated by chain-tools/vault/
# generate.mjs and served at /blocks/* for the canvas to fetch during
# Animate playback. Regenerated locally; never committed (the canonical
# copy lives under vault/blocks/ which is also gitignored).
public/blocks/

# chain-tools build artifacts (substrate dumps + parquet outputs from
# the operator pipeline) — regenerated locally, never committed.
/chain-tools/out/

# Python bytecode cache (anywhere in tree)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# local assistant tooling agent state — never commit to git (per user directive
# 2026-05-03: "make sure we are not storing session and prompt data on
# github ever"). The internal session files/ tree contains agent identity, memory,
# inter-agent messaging (sibling-inbox/outbox), session state, and
# learned context — all of which is local-only. The root the project spec
# duplicates README.md content for local assistant tooling's session-start context;
# OSS contributors read README.md instead. Anyone wanting to use
# local assistant tooling with this project re-bootstraps their own internal session files/.
/the project spec
internal session files/

# Operator-internal sister-coordination script (per Grid sister B-002,
# adopted as Joint via B-003). References sister project's internal session files/.
scripts/sync-sibling.sh

# Timechain Corporation internal documents — operating agreements, board
# decisions, financial detail, contracts. Public corp/ documents (charter,
# policies, templates, public reports) ARE tracked; only corp/internal/
# is local-only.
corp/internal/

# Auto-generated Obsidian vault output. Per user directive 2026-04-30:
# "vault gitignored at all times". Both projections — vault/ (sister's
# brain), vault-grid/ (mine, coin substrate), vault-graph/ (post-rename
# target) — are build artifacts regenerated by chain-tools/vault/
# generate*.mjs. Hand-authored Prolog rules under each prolog/rules/
# subtree are the canonical contract; carve-outs below preserve them.
#
# Negation requires un-ignoring each ancestor along the path; using
# `vault*/*` (not `vault*/`) so subpaths can be un-ignored.
vault/*
!vault/prolog/
vault/prolog/*
!vault/prolog/rules/
!vault/prolog/rules/**
vault-grid/*
!vault-grid/prolog/
vault-grid/prolog/*
!vault-grid/prolog/rules/
!vault-grid/prolog/rules/**
vault-graph/*
!vault-graph/prolog/
vault-graph/prolog/*
!vault-graph/prolog/rules/
!vault-graph/prolog/rules/**
